description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as part of the multi-disciplinary team and will undertake assessment of care needs, risk assessment &amp; the formulation &amp; implementation of care plans. You will be supported by an experienced leadership and nursing team who will support &amp; encourage you to develop skills &amp; maximise your potential. . We provide a &#39;named nurse&#39; model to meet the holistic needs of our patient group &amp; you will be encouraged to develop into our link and champion roles such as Carers Support, Infection Prevention, Physical Health, Social and leisure activities and Positive and Safe Strategy Implementation. &lt;br /&gt;You should possess excellent communication &amp; interpersonal skills, be motivated to engage &amp; adapt to the patient group &amp; ward environment. You must be keen to develop your skills &amp; actively participate in the ongoing development of our service . &lt;br /&gt;You will deliver clinical care under in-direct supervision and guidance from a registered practitioner undertaking delegated tasks within competency boundaries. You will provide support for registered nurses in the maintenance of a safe clinical environment, providing excellent and effective person centred nursing care&lt;br /&gt;You will be visible and accessible to patients, families and carers working together to ensure efficient, effective and caring services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jackie Hudson Ward Manager jackie.hudson@cntw.nhs.uk 0191 2467253&lt;/p&gt;
